args: Ta-dah! Here's your present, Luccy.\nSpoiler: it's a sweater!
It's got your name on it...AND mine!\nI tried to make it really classy.\nArtistic-like, you know?
Ta-daaah! Here's your gift for today, Luccy.\nI drew our storybook love into a literal\nstorybook!
It starts with our meeting and goes all the\nway up to when we're buried side-by-side\nin a shared grave! Oops, more spoilers!
Ta-daaaaah! Here's today's haul, Luccy!\nThe armoire in your room was getting old,\nso I had a new one custom-built for you!
Too big? Don't be silly! With all our kids\non the way, we'll need at LEAST this much\nstorage to keep everything squared away.
(Well, Chelsea DID listen to me about only\ngiving inanimate objects as presents...)
(But it's EVERY. SINGLE. DAY.\nAnd each one's more expensive\nand labor-intensive than the last.)
(I can tell she's put a ton of thought into\neach and every one, but...that's kinda the\nproblem. It's terrifying.)
(I keep looking over my shoulder,\nbracing for the next ＂token of affection.＂)
Eagh! She's back again! I've gotta hide!
Hmmmmm? Are you out and about?\nLuuuccy! Oh, Luuuuuccy!
(Hold your breath... Erase your presence...\nJust another minute, and she'll—)
I know you're iiiiin there, Luccy!\nOpen the door. Open the door, sweetie.\nOpen it. Open the door OPEN THE DOOR—
*gasp* Hrk... I'm not! I'm not here!
I know what's going on here, Luccy.\nThe door's stuck and you're trapped inside.\nBut don't you worry...
I'll pry it open with my crowbar of love.
There we go, Luccy.\nI knew you were in here, silly.
IN ILIA'S NAME I PRAY, SPARE MEEE!
Oh! Sarisse. Well, it's about yesterday...
—and then he let out the CUTEST blood-\ncurdling scream and fainted on the spot.
I see. Luca can be so insensitive at times!\nWhat kinda dunderhead freaks out when\nsomeone's only trying to give you a gift?
I wanted to make him happy, not scared...
Hmmm... So you're trying to think of a\npresent that'll brighten his spirits, huh?
Maybe something normal would work\nbest. He's a pretty simple-minded guy.
What about making some food for him?\nLike, some sweets would make an easy\ngift.
You think? I'd been avoiding food,\nseeing as I already make him meals\nall the time.
No need to worry about that. There's no\nway a gift that timeless'll go over his head!
If you think Luccy will love it, then I'm in.
Great! Mind if I join you in the kitchen?\nMelsa and I are doing a sweets exchange!
You're a total cooking whiz, so I'd love\nto have you there to help if I get stuck.
You really want to bake with me?!
(Oh gosh, I'm freaking out! But once Luccy\nand I are married, she'll be my little sis...)
Y'know? I'd love to help, Sarisse! Both\ntoday, and for many, MANY years to come.
Uh... Okay? As long as you don't mind!
Now, what to make...\nGot anything in mind yet, Chelsea?
I'm going with apple pie!\nLuccy just LOVES apples.
Aha ha ha! I figured you'd say that.\nHis taste buds are gonna be in heaven.
Now, as for me... I should probably\nmake something holiday-appropriate.
The problem is, I'm just not that familiar\nwith Valentine's Day. It's a human thing.
Roses are a traditional Valentine's gift,\nso I think that should be plenty suitable.
Huh! Great idea, Chelsea! I knew you were\nthe right girl to ask about this kinda stuff.
Oh, uh... Gosh! Ha ha. You're making\nme blush. Glad I could help!
For a sylvan, you sure are an\nexpert on this human holiday.
Yeah, I guess so. When I was little,\nI lived with my mom and dad in a human\nvillage, see.
We used to give each other Valentine's\npresents every year—as a family.
That's really sweet. You must have so\nmany happy holiday memories, then.
Yeah. It's a special day for me.\nThat's why I really wanna make\nit memorable for Luccy, too.
Awww, my brother is SO spoiled. Right—\nlet's cram all our love into these suckers!
And...done! Ha ha! I hope Melsa likes it.
How'd your apple pie come out? Whoa,\nthat looks amazing! It's got a perfectly\ngolden crust, and that smell? HEAVENLY.
It's burned here and there. Plus,\nthe dome didn't rise high enough.
Valentine's Day is special.\nThe pie has to be special, too!
Er, Chelsea...? Don't tell me you're going\nto start again from scratch?
Another dud. The ratio of apple filling\nto crust was totally skewed.
You're starting over AGAIN?\nBut it looks delicious...
Nope... This one's flawed too.\nToo much cinnamon this time.
You DO know it's almost midnight, right?\nHow many pies have you gone through?
I'll keep going till I've got the perfect apple\npie. No matter how many tries it takes.
Another dud... A failure... One more...\nJust one more...try... *mumble*
*yaaawn* Mmm, something sure\nsmells good. What's cookin'?
Whoa! It's apple pies as far as the eye\ncan see! Talk about a breakfast buffet.\nLet's have a taste... *HOMPH!*
GYAAAH! LUCCY, NO! You can't eat that!\nIt's not... It's not...!
It has a whole half-pinch too much sugar,\nthe fire was two kindling twigs too hot, and\nthe egg wash only hit 99.9%! It's not food!
Oh, hey, Chelsea. Did you bake this?\nGirl, you could WEAPONIZE pie this good!
You... You like it? You're happy, Luccy?\nEven though my pie is totally garbage-tier?
What are you talking about?\nThis is a fantastic present. I love it.
(And unlike all the others, I don't feel a\ncrushing weight bearing down on me...but\nthat's a little hard to say to her face.)
Eee... EEE HEE HEE HEE HEE!\nThis is great. Stupendous, even!
My Luccy's a bona fide pie-niac! I just\nhave to bake until the cows come home!
Sorry it took me this long to figure out\nwhat you wanted, sweetie. Thank you,\nSarisse! Thank you, Valentine's Day!
From now on, I'll bake you desserts for all\nthree meals, plus afternoon and midnight\nsnacks!
Ooh, I'd better get started planting\nthe apple orchard for next year!\nThe wheat field for the flour I'll need, too.
Uh, you REALLY don't have to do all that.
EeE HeE hEe HeE! Eventually, your entire\ndiet will consist of nothing but food\nI've lovingly grown from the ground up!
Ah, yes. There's that old,\nfamiliar terror setting in again.
